rss collector written in c

used libraries:

	curl
	libxml2
	sqlite3

howto:

$ tar zxf rssroll.tar.gz

$ cd rssroll

## edit index.c
static char             *baseurl = "https://blogroll.chaosophia.net/index.cgi";
## change it with your url
static char             *mailaddr = "koue@chaosophia.net";
## change mail
static char             *dbname = "/srv/rss.db";
## change path to the sqlite rss db. 

$ make
( there is no configure so if there is error during compilation 
  probably its caused by missing library or wrong "include" or
  "library" path in Makefile.)

## create sqlite database
$ sqlite3 rssroll.db < create_database.sql

## create categories
$ sqlite3 rssroll.db "insert into categories (title) values ('news')"
$ sqlite3 rssroll.db "insert into categories (title) values ('tech')"

## add channels from parsing
$ sqlite3 rssroll.db "insert into channels (catid, modified, link) values (2, 123456, 'http://www.freebsd.org/security/rss.xml')"
## catid = 2 (tech category), modified = 123456 (random value, this is the latest parsing timestamp), link of the rss file

## parse the feeds
$ ./rssroll -d ./rssroll.db

## put index.cgi in your web dir

example:
https://blogroll.chaosophia.net/index.cgi

